  <!-- ══ MISSION ══ -->
  <section class="js-mission">
    <div class="js-wrap">
      <div class="js-mission-inner">
        <div>
          <div class="js-mission-label">Our Doctrine</div>
          <div class="js-mission-title">Why We Show Up</div>
        </div>
        <div class="js-mission-body">
          <p>The legal system is not neutral. It never has been. For Black Americans, the courthouse has too often been a place where innocence is irrelevant, where wealth determines freedom, where the community watches from the outside while one of their own is processed inside.</p>
          <p><strong>E5 Enclave's Justice Support vertical exists to change that equation.</strong> We believe that every person who has been wrongly targeted, unjustly prosecuted, or unfairly imprisoned deserves more than a lawyer. They deserve a community that shows up — in the gallery, at the bond hearing, at the front door.</p>
          <p>We provide <em>court presence</em> — organized, peaceful, sustained community witness that reminds judges, prosecutors, and juries that someone is watching and that someone cares.</p>
          <p>We provide <em>bail and bond relief</em> — direct financial assistance and advocacy to keep innocent people out of pretrial detention while their cases proceed.</p>
          <p>We provide <em>holistic care</em> — because the person on trial is not alone in their suffering. Their family suffers. Their children suffer. Their community suffers. We meet all of it.</p>
          <p>And we provide <em>protection</em> — because harassment, doxxing, and intimidation of families and their advocates has become a tool of suppression. We do not allow our people to face that alone.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

